I’ve always loved reading @bodha’s newsletters and this last one particularly resonated for me. In hope, that you don’t mind me quoting your beautiful wise words @bodha 

“Lately, I find myself coming across opposing moments in people's lives - on one side are those distressed to realize they've lost touch with themselves. And on the other side are those grateful to find they've become a good friend to themselves. 

It got me thinking about what having a deeper relationship with yourself means and what might help me/us go in that direction. So far, I've come up with three themes

Specificity - getting more specific about what you like rather than 'time in nature,' perhaps it's 'time in remote, rugged landscapes'. Leigh from Moon Lists suggests making a 'Most Me' list for when you need a reminder of who you are.

Discomfort - spending time doing things outside your usual routines & activities. 

Noticing - activities that increase your ability to notice because, as Susan Sontag said, 'Attention is vitality'. Perhaps it's a walk alone, a gallery visit, looking out the window.”

Do you have any other thoughts?
